725876f-a.text:

725877f.title: Queens: 144th Street - 89th Avenue
725877f.text:
144th Street (left), at the N.E. corner of Eimhty-ninth Ave.,
showing the residence of Abraham Kettletas 1780, or that of S. Judd
of 1846. The wings of this structure were removed prior to moving
this structure from its original site in Jamaica Ave.
Rev. Abraham Kettletas, born in New York in 1732, was a Pres-
byterian Minister, who came to Jamaica on or about the year 1759.
He had no pastorate, but occupied a farm near the site of tcis house.
During the Revolution the British took possession of his property and
defaced his home. In 1799 there is a probability that the house of
the late William Kettletas burned to the ground and that S. Judd erected
the present structure.
1922.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection.
